its\nmetal, or was stolen is not clear.  Probably no one will ever know.\n'),(3705,'lamppost','  A dull <k>black<1> finish covers this <k>lamppost<1> but the most\nnoticeable part of this is the streaks of <r>red<1> running down its side.\nOn first glance, it appears to be <o>rust<1>.  However, the <o>rust<1> is\nalmost the color of <r>blood<1> which is equally likely.\n'),(3760,'lamppost','  A dull <k>black finish<1> covers this lamppost which clearly shows the\naffects of the elements.  It appears lucky to still be working.\n'),(3791,'block','This block seems to be slightly out of place, jutting out ever so slightly\nfrom the wall.  Filled with sudden inspiration, you try pulling with little\nsuccess.  Yet the way it barely moved felt as if it was hinged.  Maybe you\ncould pick the block out with a weapon or something...\n'),(3798,'femur bone','This well-eaten bone bears little resemblance to whatever poor creature\nit was in life.  Deep claw marks gouge its surface, and the rest of the\nbone has been stripped clean of flesh.\n'),(3801,'cloak','<k>A cloak of pitch black onyx.<1>\n'),(3812,'helm onyx','It looks like a standard <k>helmet<1> made of pure <k>onyx<1>.\n'),(3898,'bracer obsidian','It seems to absorb the light somewhat.\n'),(3899,'sword obsidian darkness','It glows with its own dark light as it absorbs the surrounding light.\n'),(4304,'staff Bullywug ceremonial leaves leaf mosses wood','Made of a sturdy swamp wood the staff is about two inches in diameter\nand approximately four feet in length.  All along its length are a\ncollection of mosses and leaves collected from the swamp most likely.\nThe staff doesn\'t appear to have any other features which catch your\neye.\n'),(4307,'trough muddy water','Slightly <k>muddy<1> <b>water<1> festers by the side of the road here.  It\nlooks like it is drinkable...barely drinkable.\n'),(4308,'tree cypress large','  This <g>tree<1> is one of the largest of its kind in the <k>swamp<1>,\nand older than you can imagine. 